    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - HARD START AND NO START DIAGNOSTICS - Test Procedures - Main Power
        Relay Voltage to ECM
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="4">
        <title>Main Power Relay Voltage to ECM</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f2400539" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D3166.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Purpose</emph>
            </para>
            <para>To determine correct power supplied to operate the ECM. The ECM requires 7 volts minimum to operate
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Relay breakout harness</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DMM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                        safety instructions in the foreword of this manual. Follow all warnings, cautions, and notes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Batteries must be fully charged before doing the following procedures.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Voltage Measurement with Breakout harness at Main Power Relay</title>
            <figure id="f2400540" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D3120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Relay breakout harness installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn all accessories off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install relay breakout harness between ECM power relay and power distribution box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect DMM POS to lead 87 and NEG to ground post on cowl.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Crank engine for 20 seconds and measure voltage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Record the lowest voltage on Hard Start and No Start Diagnostics form .</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If the voltage is below 7 volts, the ECM power relay may be resetting, resulting from low
                            voltage and current from the batteries or problems in the ignition circuit or power feed
                            circuits. See Electronic Control Module Power (ECM PWR) in Section 7.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Low battery voltage: defective batteries, high resistance at battery cable connections or in
                        wiring to the ECM
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Low or no battery voltage to the ECM: high resistance or an open power feed circuit to the ECM
                        or ECM power relay. The ECM power circuit fuse in battery box may be open, or the ECM power
                        relay may be defective.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>V
                        <subscript>IGN</subscript>
                        circuit problem
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Defective ECM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Voltage Measurement at ECM with Breakout Box</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Breakout box</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DMM</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn off all accessories.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 2 white connectors (X3 and X4) from ECM.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2400541" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31153.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Breakout box installed</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install breakout box connectors (X3 and X4) to connections on ECM.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect chassis harness connectors to breakout box header (X3 and X4).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2400542" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D3189.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Breakout box</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect leads of the DMM to the following test points on the breakout box:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>POS X3 - 3 to NEG X3 - 7 ( V
                            <subscript>IGN</subscript>
                            Pwr)
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>POS X4 - 2 to NEG X3 - 7 (ECM Pwr)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>POS X4 - 1 to NEG X3 - 7 (ECM Pwr)</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Crank engine for 20 seconds and measure voltage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Record the lowest voltage on Hard Start and No Start Diagnostics form .</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If the voltage is below 7 volts, the ECM power relay may be resetting, resulting from low
                            voltage and current from the batteries or problems in the ignition circuit or power feed
                            circuits. See Electronic Control Module Power (ECM PWR) in Section 7.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
